    "body": "OpenZeppelin bug bounty is about finding a security vulnerability that allows somebody else remotely exploit the contract code, not about the inherent issue with the underlying standards (i.e. ERC-20). If you found a problem with a standard like ERC-20, good for you but you're not the first to notice this. It's been documented for years already.\r\n\r\nERC-20 is far from ideal. In fact, it's one of the foolish designs I've ever encountered in my whole software development career.",
